title: fanoutqa: What are the official websites of the five most populous cities in the world? (f3a8115bcfb58655)

chat_history.content: What are the official websites of the five most populous cities in the world?

Here are the official websites of the five most populous cities in the world:

1. Tokyo, Japan: There is no single official website for the city of Tokyo. Instead, various websites provide information about different aspects of the city. Some of these include:

   - [Tokyo Metropolitan Government Website](https://www.metro.tokyo.lg.jp/ENGLISH/) This site covers government-related information, including policies, statistics, and news related to Tokyo's administration.

   - [Tokyo Tourism Official Website](https://www.gotokyo.org/) This website promotes tourism in Tokyo, offering travel guides, event information, and recommendations for attractions, dining, and shopping.

   - [Tokyo 2020 Olympics Official Website](https://tokyo2020.org/) While the Olympics have already taken place, this website still provides historical information and archives related to the 2020 Tokyo Olympics.

   

2. Shanghai, China: [Shanghai Municipal People's Government](https://www.shanghai.gov.cn/) (in Chinese) is the official website of the Shanghai city government, providing information on government policies, news, public services, and more. The website is primarily in Chinese, but an English version is available with limited content.

3. Beijing, China: [Beijing Municipal Government](http://www.beijing.gov.cn/) is the official website of the Beijing city administration. It provides information on government services, policies, news, and resources for residents and visitors. The website is mainly in Chinese, but an English version is available with a limited range of content.

4. Mexico City, Mexico: [Mexico City Government](http://www.cdmx.gob.mx/) (in Spanish) is the official website of the Mexico City government. It offers information on government services, programs, culture, tourism, and more. The website is primarily in Spanish, but an English version is also available.

5. Dhaka, Bangladesh: The official website of the Dhaka city government is not readily available or easily accessible. However, here are a few relevant websites:

   - [Dhaka North City Corporation](https://www.dncc.gov.bd/) This site provides information on services and initiatives related to the northern part of Dhaka.

   - [Dhaka South City Corporation](https://www.dscc.gov.bd/) This website offers information and services related to the southern part of Dhaka.

   - [Dhaka Metropolitan Police](https://www.dhakametropolitanpolice.gov.bd/) The official website of the Dhaka Metropolitan Police provides information on law enforcement, traffic, and public safety.
